text: A video shows Matt Hancock saying the WHO told him there is no evidence for asymptomatic transmission of Covid-19.
Transmission of COVID-19 by asymptomatic individuals has never been proven.
A post shared on Facebook attributes to Cornell University professor Dr. Robert Oswald a lengthy quote that states in part, COVID-19 does not exist and is fictitious.
Study shows asymptomatic transmission of Covid-19 didn’t happen at all
Asymptomatic transmission of Covid-19 is a hoax.
There's no evidence there is a Covid-19 virus. The illusion of it has been manifested by using a fake test and fraudulent death certificates.
Says there is no COVID-19 virus.
Says a recent study found no asymptomatic or presymptomatic spread of COVID.
